wdi2-SL.SRV.EMPL.FE.ZS.def: Employment is defined as persons of working age who were engaged in any activity to produce goods or provide services for pay or profit, whether at work during the reference period or not at work due to temporary absence from a job, or to working-time arrangement. The services sector consists of wholesale and retail trade and restaurants and hotels; transport, storage, and communications; financing, insurance, real estate, and business services; and community, social, and personal services, in accordance with divisions 6-9 (ISIC 2) or categories G-Q (ISIC 3) or categories G-U (ISIC 4).
wdi2-SL.SRV.EMPL.FE.ZS.name: Employment in services
wdi2-SL.SRV.EMPL.FE.ZS.source: International Labour Organization, ILOSTAT database. Data retrieved on January 29, 2021.
